# Voomie tool descriptions — example stub

This is an `.example` file. The real tool descriptions are loaded from
`prompts/voomie_tools.md` at runtime via the `VOOMIE_TOOLS_PROMPT_PATH`
environment variable. The real file is gitignored because the
descriptions are shop-specific tool-routing prose — they tell the LLM
when to call each tool in the context of your shop's DSL and policies.

# Loader contract

Each H2 header (`## <tool_name>`) starts a new tool block. The block
body is read as plain text (no substitution) and injected as the
FunctionDeclaration's `description=` argument. Tool names must match
the FunctionDeclaration `name=` exactly. Missing or extra tools cause
the loader to fail loud at agent import time.

The 11 tool names expected (matching the FunctionDeclaration objects in
`voomie/agent.py`):

  parse_shoptalk
  query_stock_registry
  query_press_registry
  lookup_customer
  create_customer
  update_job_status
  append_conversation_turn
  persist_job
  flag_for_human
  inspect_pdf
  render_preview

# Stub entries (replace each with your shop's real description)

## parse_shoptalk

Parse a spec source program with your shop's DSL parser. Describe the success/failure return shape, key field constraints, and any non-obvious tool behavior (e.g. dimensional bounds, type discriminators).

## query_stock_registry

Describe when the agent should call this tool. Surface the criteria
keys, the match-tier semantics, and how to react to ambiguous matches.

## query_press_registry

Same shape — when to call, what to pass, what to do with results.

## lookup_customer

Describe the lookup behavior and the response shapes for hit/miss.

## create_customer

Describe the create flow including pre-condition (call only after a miss),
return shapes, and error cases.

## update_job_status

List the allowed phase strings. Note when this tool will fail (e.g.,
job not yet persisted) so the agent sequences its calls correctly.

## append_conversation_turn

Document the role taxonomy and any caps (turn limits, etc.).

## persist_job

Document required fields, side effects, and idempotency guarantees.

## flag_for_human

Describe the terminal-state escalation conditions exactly — this is the
load-bearing CSR-handoff contract.

## inspect_pdf

Document the return shapes for PDF-vs-non-PDF inputs and what the agent
should do with non-PDF detections.

## render_preview

Describe when to call (e.g., explicit user request only) and the
constraint that the action_plan must be parser-output verbatim.
